Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Mason City is recognized as the largest city in the Northern Iowa region, and is equidistant between Minneapolis and Des Moines. The community serves as the cultural, entertainment and economic center for the nine county region. Mason City is known for its stable economy and for serving the region’s retail, manufacturing and trade sectors. Area businesses also benefit from Mason City’s location near the intersection of major Interstate 35 and 90 and its regional airport.  With a mix of local colleges and technical training institutions, Mason City also helps to educate the highly-skilled workforce located in Northern Iowa.
